1
00:00:00,591 --> 00:00:02,212
Our course has three main parts.

2
00:00:02,552 --> 00:00:05,532
The first part is working with financial data in Python.

3
00:00:06,273 --> 00:00:13,154
In this part, we'll learn how to read historical financial data into Python, organize it, manipulate it, and then analyze it.

4
00:00:13,674 --> 00:00:19,276
We'll also use Python to visualize financial data so we can see patterns more clearly.

5
00:00:19,756 --> 00:00:22,217
The second part is computational investing.

6
00:00:22,737 --> 00:00:27,378
In this part, we'll study the methods and models used in data-driven investing.

7
00:00:28,114 --> 00:00:36,238
We'll look at ideas used by hedge funds, investment banks, and trading teams to work with financial data and make investment decisions.

8
00:00:36,899 --> 00:00:39,940
The third part is machine learning methods for trading.

9
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:43,422
In this final part, we will bring everything together.

10
00:00:43,943 --> 00:00:53,528
We'll take the financial data skills from the first part, the investment concepts from the second part, and then apply machine learning methods to trading problems.

11
00:00:54,148 --> 00:01:05,044
We'll use and discuss algorithms such as Random Forest and QLearning and we'll see how these tools can be used to build trading strategies.

12
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:18,839
My goal is that after you complete this course, you will be prepared to contribute to a trading system development team, such as at a hedge fund and investment bank or a financial technology company.

13
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:28,624
You should be able to work with financial data and you should be able to analyze them, build models, test ideas, and think carefully about the results.

14
00:01:29,105 --> 00:01:31,966
At the same time, I want to be clear about one thing.

15
00:01:32,422 --> 00:01:39,569
Completing this course does not mean you should immediately start automated trading with real money.

16
00:01:40,009 --> 00:01:41,551
The course is a starting point.

17
00:01:41,831 --> 00:01:48,258
It will give you the foundation to understand how these systems are built and what it takes to use them responsibly.

